vulnerabilities.title: Insufficient Documentation of Error Handling Techniques
vulnerabilities.description:
## Overview

Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Insufficient Documentation of Error Handling Techniques in the `ParseWithClaims` function. An attacker can exploit this to accept invalid tokens by only checking for specific errors and ignoring others.

## Workaround

Users who are not able to upgrade to the fixed version should make sure that they are properly checking for all errors, see [`example_test.go`](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/blob/bc8bdca5cced1caa9787e4a1c313a3538544c877/example_test.go#L165-L189)
## Remediation
Upgrade `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v4` to version 4.5.1 or higher.
## References
- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/commit/7b1c1c00a171c6c79bbdb40e4ce7d197060c1c2c)

vulnerabilities.title: Allocation of Resources Without Limits or Throttling
vulnerabilities.description:
## Overview
[go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/github.com/emicklei/go-restful/otelrestful](https://pkg.go.dev/go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/github.com/emicklei/go-restful/otelrestful) is an instruments github.com/emicklei/go-restful.

Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Allocation of Resources Without Limits or Throttling via the `otelhttp` handler wrapper. An attacker can cause a denial of service by sending numerous malicious requests with random and long `http.user_agent` and `http.method` labels.

**Note:**

This is only exploitable if the program uses the `otelhttp.NewHandler` wrapper and does not filter any unknown HTTP methods or User agents at the CDN, LB, previous middleware, etc. level.

## Workaround

This vulnerability can be mitigated by using `otelhttp.WithFilter()`, but it requires manual careful configuration to not log certain requests entirely.
## Remediation
Upgrade `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/github.com/emicklei/go-restful/otelrestful` to version 0.44.0 or higher.
## References
- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-go-contrib/commit/50ca48f8017e04bcf9149a5435e7f8f96f9e83c9)
- [GitHub PR](https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-go-contrib/pull/4277)
- [GitHub Release](https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-go-contrib/releases/tag/v1.19.0)
